    "asOf": "2003-04-02",
    "date": "2006-11-28T17:35:40Z",
    "text": "Help and Opportunities for Parents of Exceptional Children Act of 2003 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow an annual tax credit of up to $3,000 (with adjustments for inflation) per year for the qualified elementary or secondary education expenses of a dependent child with a disability.Includes private, parochial, religious, or home schools among qualified educational institutions."
